ould try going west.", "room_type": "storage", "definite": null, "indefinite": null, "synonyms": null}], ["r_7", {"id": "r_7", "type": "r", "name": "kitchen", "noun": "kitchen", "adj": null, "desc": "You are in a kitchen. An usual kind of place. The room seems oddly familiar, as though it were only superficially different from the other rooms in the building.\n\n\n\nThere is an exit to the east. Don't worry, it is unguarded. There is an unblocked exit to the south.", "room_type": "cook", "definite": null, "indefinite": null, "synonyms": null}], ["r_3", {"id": "r_3", "type": "r", "name": "bedchamber", "noun": "bedchamber", "adj": null, "desc": "I never took you for the sort of person who would show up in a bedchamber, but I guess I was wrong.\n\n\n\nYou don't like doors? Why not try going north, that entranceway is unblocked. There is an unblocked exit to the south.", "room_type": "rest", "definite": null, "indefinite": null, "synonyms": null}], ["r_8", {"id": "r_8", "type": "r", "name": "studio", "noun": "studio", "adj": null, "desc": "You find yourself in a studio. A typical kind of place. You begin to take stock of what's in the room.\n\n\n\nThere is an unguarded exit to the north. You don't like doors? Why not try going south, that entranceway is unblocked.", "room_type": "work", "definite": null, "indefinite": null, "synonyms": null}], ["r_9", {"id": "r_9", "type": "r", "name": "study", "noun": "study", "adj": null, "desc": "You've just sauntered into a study. You begin to take stock of what's here.\n\n\n\nThere is an unblocked exit to the north.", "room_type": "work", "definite": null, "indefinite": null, "synonyms": null}], ["o_0", {"id": "o_0", "type": "o", "name": "coin", "noun": null, "adj": null, "desc": "The coin is unremarkable.", "room_type": "work", "definite": null, "indefinite": null, "synonyms": null}]], "KB": {"logic": "# thing\ntype t {\n    rules {\n        examine/t :: at(P, r) & $at(t, r) -> at(P, r);\n    }\n\n    reverse_rules {\n        examine/t :: examine/t;\n    }\n\n    inform7 {\n        type {\n            kind :: \"thing\";\n        }\n\n        commands {\n            examine/t :: \"examine {t}\" :: \"examining the {t}\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n# room\ntype r {\n    predicates {\n        at(P, r);\n        at(t, r);\n\n        north_of(r, r);\n        west_of(r, r);\n\n        free(r, r);\n\n        south_of(r, r') = north_of(r', r);\n        east_of(r, r') = west_of(r', r);\n    }\n\n    rules {\n        go/north :: at(P, r) & $north_of(r', r) & $free(r, r') & $free(r', r) -> at(P, r');\n        go/south :: at(P, r) & $south_of(r', r) & $free(r, r') & $free(r', r) -> at(P, r');\n        go/east  :: at(P, r) & $east_of(r', r) & $free(r, r') & $free(r', r) -> at(P, r');\n        go/west  :: at(P, r) & $west_of(r', r) & $free(r, r') & $free(r', r) -> at(P, r');\n    }\n\n    reverse_rules {\n        go/north :: go/south;\n        go/west :: go/east;\n    }\n\n    constraints {\n        r1 :: at(P, r) & at(P, r') -> fail();\n\n        # An exit direction can only lead to one room.\n        nav_rr1 :: north_of(r, r') & north_of(r'', r') -> fail();\n        nav_rr2 :: south_of(r, r') & south_of(r'', r') -> fail();\n        nav_rr3 :: east_of(r, r') & east_of(r'', r') -> fail();\n        nav_rr4 :: west_of(r, r') & west_of(r'', r') -> fail();\n\n        # Two rooms can only be connected once with each other.\n        nav_rrA :: north_of(r, r') & south_of(r, r') -> fail();\n        nav_rrB :: north_of(r, r') & west_of(r, r') -> fail();\n        nav_rrC :: north_of(r, r') & east_of(r, r') -> fail();\n        nav_rrD :: south_of(r, r') & west_of(r, r') -> fail();\n        nav_rrE :: south_of(r, r') & east_of(r, r') -> fail();\n        nav_rrF :: west_of(r, r')  & east_of(r, r') -> fail();\n    }\n\n    inform7 {\n        type {\n            kind :: \"room\";\n        }\n\n        predicates {\n            at(P, r) :: \"The player is in {r}\";\n            at(t, r) :: \"The {t} is in {r}\";\n            free(r, r') :: \"\";  # No equivalent in Inform7.\n\n            north_of(r, r') :: \"The {r} is mapped north of {r'}\";\n            south_of(r, r') :: \"The {r} is mapped south of {r'}\";\n            east_of(r, r') :: \"The {r} is mapped east of {r'}\";\n            west_of(r, r') :: \"The {r} is mapped west of {r'}\";\n        }\n\n        commands {\n            go/north :: \"go north\" :: \"going north\";\n            go/south :: \"go south\" :: \"going south\";\n            go/east :: \"go east\" :: \"going east\";\n            go/west :: \"go west\" :: \"going west\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n# Inventory\ntype I {\n    predicates {\n        in(o, I);\n    }\n\n    rules {\n        take :: $at(P, r) & at(o, r) -> in(o, I);\n        drop :: $at(P, r) & in(o, I) -> at(o, r);\n        inventory :: at(P, r) -> at(P, r);  # Nothing changes.\n        examine/I :: in(o, I) -> in(o, I);  # Nothing changes.\n    }\n\n    reverse_rules {\n        inventory :: inventory;\n        take :: drop;\n        examine/I :: examine/I;\n    }\n\n    inform7 {\n        predicates {\n            in(o, I) :: \"The player carries the {o}\";\n        }\n\n        commands {\n            take :: \"take {o}\" :: \"taking the {o}\";\n            drop :: \"drop {o}\" :: \"dropping the {o}\";\n            inventory :: \"inventory\" :: \"taking inventory\";\n            examine/I :: \"examine {o}\" :: \"examining the {o}\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n# Player\ntype P {\n    rules {\n        look :: at(P, r) -> at(P, r);  # Nothing changes.\n    }\n\n    reverse_rules {\n        look :: look;\n    }\n\n    inform7 {\n        commands {\n            look :: \"look\" :: \"looking\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n# object\ntype o : t {\n    constraints {\n        obj1 :: in(o, I) & at(o, r) -> fail();\n        obj2 :: at(o, r) & at(o, r') -> fail();\n    }\n\n    inform7 {\n        type {\n            kind :: \"object-like\";\n            definition :: \"object-like is portable.\";\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n", "text_grammars_path": "/home/cyrchanh/coin-collector/venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/textworld/challenges/tw_coin_collector/textworld_data/text_grammars"}, "metadata": {"walkthrough": ["go west", "go west", "go south", "go south", "go west", "go south", "go west", "go south", "go south", "take coin"], "desc": "Coin Collector", "mode": "simple", "seeds": {"map": 33811, "objects": 39220, "quest": 17738, "grammar": 17218}, "world_size": 10, "quest_length": 10, "uuid": "tw-coin_collector-b9i7c9-house-mo-VLpEiW2msKJpTZ7J"}, "objective": "Hey, thanks for coming over to the TextWorld today, there is something I need you to do for me. First of all, make an attempt to venture west. Then, travel west. If you can accomplish that, head south. With that over with, make an effort to move south. Then, attempt to head west. And then, move south. That done, make an effort to move west. Then, venture south. With that accomplished, attempt to go to the south. With that accomplished, recover the coin from the floor of the study. And once you've done that, you win!"}